text: The thirty-fourth government of Israel was installed on May 14, 2015 and ended on May 17, 2020. Prime minister was Likud politician Benjamin Netanyahu. Participating parties (with seats in the 20th Knesset in brackets): * HaLikud (Likud) (30) * Kulanu (10) * HaBayit HaYehudi (The Jewish Home) (8) * Shas (7) * Yahadut HaTorah (United Torah Judaism) (6) * Yisrael Beiteinu (5) One Yisrael Beiteinu politician left the party. The Fourth Netanyahu Government can be characterized as a right-wing government with a great religious contribution. == References == == Other websites == * Government 34, Knesset website * Government 34, Israeli Ministry of Foreign Affairs website Category:Israeli governments Category:2015 establishments in Israel Category:Benjamin Netanyahu
title: Thirty-fourth government of Israel
